      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>The plantation in this letter was most likely Refuge
         Plantation in Camden County, Georgia.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>Letter, dated 6 November 1864, from a slave named Sipe to
         his master, regarding the care of the plantation while the
         family was gone, forgaging by the Union soldiers, and Sipe's
         attempts to protect the property.</p>
      </scopecontent>
